formatted_address: 2 Changi Business Park Ave 1, #01-02 Hotel Tower, UE BizHub East, Singapore 486015
name: The Manchurian Club

reviews.text:
The food is great here. A lot of options for vegetarian dishes.
Must try dish is Salt and pepper corn, chilli pepper paneer, Szechwan Noodles
The staff needs some training to be away from customer’s tables while they are dining as it may intervene in their privacy.
The food is good, hot n spicy soup, apptising starters and great lunch spot amidst busy workspaces

Food is very very good n suitable for all ages n not spice.
Order Szechwan fried rice n noodle n also veg machurian.
Delivery by grab was also on time n prompt
Must try pepper chilli fish excellent
Nasir fish also good
But expensive for the quality they serve

Dessert best is Sizzlingly brownie but tiramisu not good if u choose brownie
we frequently order the corn salt and pepper and it’s always good, this time i tried the steamed chicken wantons and loved them too

A decent and spacious outlet for Indo-chinese cuisine. Quick serve is a plus when you make your order from the table.

You are being checked often for any of your immediate needs by having by frequent visits by the servers to the table.

Most of the items are good and tasty but certain items are too saucy. Nevertheless the taste over shoots the saucy.

Lots of options for vegetarian people and absolutely kids friendly.

Water is not served but should be bought as bottle water.

vicinity: 2 Changi Business Park Avenue 1, #01-02 Hotel Tower, UE BizHub East
